      "enable_comment": true,
      "disabled": false,
      "comment_placeholder": "",
      "value": "9",
      "scale": 9
    },
    "comment": ""
  }],
  "value": "9",
  "value_with_comment": "9",
  "created_timestamp": 1568715275
}
```

### Attributes
Field | Type | Description
--------- | ------- | -----------
id | string | Unique identifier for answer.
question.id | string | Unique identifier for question.
question.type | enum ([Survey Question Type](#survey-respondents-enums-survey-question-type)) | Type for question.
question.variant | enum ([Survey Question Variant](#survey-respondents-enums-survey-question-variant)) | Variant for question.
question.mode | enum ([Survey Question Mode](#survey-respondents-enums-survey-question-mode)) | Mode for question.
question.title | string | Question title.
text_value | string | Text value for answer. Will be specified if question type is `TEXT`.
choices[].id | string | Unique identifier for choice.
choices[].option | object ([Survey Question Option Object](#survey-respondents-survey-question-option-object)) | Selected option for answer.
choices[].comment | string | Added comment for choice.
value | string | Normalized value in text string. This is especially useful if you want to display `choices` in text. For multiple selections, <code>&#124;&#124;</code> will be used as delimiter.
value_with_comment | string | Same as `value` but with comment appended (if there are any).
created_timestamp | integer | Timestamp when answer is added.


## Survey Question Option Object
Represents a survey question option object. This will be used for question type `SELECTION` and `SCALE`.

```json
{
  "id": "bqm4hz6i51u5gvq",
  "label": "",
  "enable_comment": true,
  "disabled": false,
  "comment_placeholder": "",
  "value": "9",
  "scale": 9
}
```

### Attributes
Field | Type | Description
--------- | ------- | -----------
id | string | Unique identifier for question option.
label | string | Label for question option.
enable_comment | boolean | If `true`, respondent can add comment for option.
disabled | boolean | If `true`, option will be disabled for selection.
comment_placeholder | string | Placeholder text for comment.
value | string | User-specified value to identify selected option.
scale | integer | Scale value for option ranging from 0 to 10. Will be provided for `SCALE` question type.


## Enums
List of available enum types under this resource.

### Survey Question Type
Value | Description
--------- | -------
TEXT | Questions that requires text input as answer.
SELECTION | Question with selection options. Will use checkboxes or radio buttons.
SCALE | Scale related questions like NPS, CSAT, CES, Smileys and 5-star Ratings.

### Survey Question Variant
Value | Description
--------- | -------
SINGLE_SELECTION | Question with single selected answer. Similar to radio buttons. Available for question type `SELECTION`.
MULTIPLE_SELECTIONS | Question with multiple selected answers. Similar to checkbox. Available for question type `SELECTION`.
SINGLE_LINE_TEXT | Question with 1 line answer. Similar to input. Available for question type `TEXT`.
MULTI_LINE_TEXT | Question with multi-line answer. Similar to textarea. Available for question type `TEXT`.
EMAIL | Question that requires email as answer. Available for question type `TEXT`.
URL | Question that requires url as answer. Available for question type `TEXT`.
BINARY_SCALE | 2 options available for selections. Examples: Happy/Sad Smileys, Like/Dislike, Recommend/Doesn't Recommend, Agree/Disagree. Available for question type `SCALE`.
THREE_POINT_SCALE | 3 options available for selections. Examples: Great/Neutral/Bad, Like/Neutral/Dislike. Available for question type `SCALE`.
FIVE_POINT_SCALE | 5 options available for selections. Examples: 5-Star Ratings, CSAT. Available for question type `SCALE`.
NPS | NPS question with answer ranging from 0 to 10. Available for question type `SCALE`.

### Survey Question Mode
Value | Description
--------- | -------
TEXT_OPTIONS | Use text to display options for questions.
NUMERIC_OPTIONS | Use numeric values to display options for questions.
REACTIONS | Use smileys to display options for questions.
STAR_RATINGS | Use 5-star ratings to display options for questions.


